    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-10-05T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-10-05T03:00:00-05:00" n="327"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/8223: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-05T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 5, 1936—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 5—1:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>295. General Chiang Kai Shek arrived Nanking this afternoon. No interview with
                    the Japanese Ambassador arranged as yet so far as can be learned.
                        Kuwashima,<note n="31" xml:id="d327fn31">Kozue Kuwashima, director of the
                        East Asiatic Bureau, Japanese Foreign Office.</note> special emissary of the
                    Japanese Foreign Office to the Japanese Ambassador, is expected in Nanking
                    morning of October 6.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department and Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Peck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
